author: @reese0526
text:
I hope this is an opportunity to remind members (not an opening to attack them):

1) the comments about Mingyu's & Woozi's stark skin color contrast; he was laughing but his eyes were frantic and wanting to switch topic quickly. it's either he's uncomfortable about it or he is aware this is a sensitive topic that could get members in trouble even if he is the one in the center of the "joke" that's why he wants to change topic.

2) I don't know why DK saw it funny or necessary to bring it up. If he didn't comment on it, nobody would have spoken about it. For being known as a sulky member he sure should know how people's feeling could get hurt easily... was it easy to talk about because it was Mingyu?

3) this statement "Mingyu you shouldn't stand next to Woozi" - why does Mingyu have to adjust? Why can't they say that Woozi shouldn't also stand next to Mingyu bcs he is so pale(and there's nothing wrong abt it too)? Why is the initial response for the darker colored person to adjust? is it because of colorism? We know they are all friends but even as outsiders fans will find it uncomfortable bcs it means they could also have same views for normal people. Ultimately, these kids should stop picking on Mingyu's skin color to stop hurting other people too.

4) these statements "how is it such a contrast?" "how is it possible?" - well people of different color other than PALE exists? why does it seem like people of darker color should not exist in their idol realm? when they literally see darker colored fans in fansigns and concerts... It's also not like his darker skin is being unhealthy? Mingyu is one of the known health buffs of the groups and he is active in outdoor sports even as a kid that's why his skin is like this. If u somehow saw his sister her skin color is very fair. So why is it such a thing to comment on even in between friends especially if they are of different skin colors. I get dark color people can comment on each other but this display is just mind-boggling to me because the way I perceived this is that having darker skin is such a letdown.

5) LASTLY, this is my own perception. I don't know what is behind all this but we all have to admit too if something they do makes us uncomfortable. We can freely ask questions especially if it's a culture so foreign to our own and seeking for understanding is so valid.
Dk laughs because it's mingyu himself who points out the color contrast between wz and him, then Dk suggests it's because of the light contrast and doesn't say anything else.

text:
Hi Going Seventeen team, this is Carat.

We would like to express our gratitude for all the hard work you put into always presenting such amazing content for Carat. The content is always entertaining and filled with love. We can feel the chemistry between Going Seventeen and the SEVENTEEN members, even though you're behind in camera.

If it weren't for you, we might not have been able to experience the happiness of the members.

Thank you also for treating the members fairly. In every Going Seventeen episode, we never feel that any member stands out more than others or gets left behind—everyone is treated equally. 

We apologize Pledis, but we feel that the Going Seventeen team does a better job of treating the SEVENTEEN members.

We hope the Going Seventeen team and SEVENTEEN can continue to work together for a long time. Please take care of and love our SEVENTEEN.

Don’t forget to take care of your health, get enough sleep, and eat regularly, because facing 13 special members will require a lot of energy 😂❤

With love, 
CARAT
